			It is said to be extremely quiet in the water. </p>
		<p> When we were waiting for the pick -up service at the meeting point in front of the campsite shortly before 8 a.m., a young couple from Germany joined us.
			They had booked the same tour. 
			We quickly got into conversation and when the lady of the driving service gave us travel tips and squeezed us with questions about our travels, the mood was quickly at the top. </p>
		<p> When we arrived at the harbor, we had to fill out a few forms before we finally started.
			First we went to Point Bay, where we made a short hike to two viewing platforms.
			From there we had a beautiful view over the Bay of Whithaven.
			Unfortunately we have reached the top of the floods and we could only see the winding waterways indicated in the color of the water.
			Yesterday we flew over it at low water and it looked very different here. </p>
