        <p> After everyone had done the obligatory photos, we went back to the board and we made our way to the beach of Whithaven.
			On the way there there were still a few larger waves.
			However, the skipper did a really good job and stabilized the boat again immediately by clever steering maneuvers. </p>
        <p> Once on the beach, we made 4 comfortable in the sand and now had 2 hours to fry in the sun and finally eat something.
			In the meantime, it looked shortly after rain, but after we had blown away the clouds, the sun quickly came out. </p>
		<p> Finally, the bullet went to a really nice snorkeling area.
			Of course, I immediately searched for anemones and the right residents (Nemo and Dori).
			Unfortunately both were not to be found. Unfortunately, Steffi was not lucky enough to search.
			The other two were not lucky with Nemo either, but they were lucky enough to meet a turtle.
			Thanks to the Zyklone Debbie, these cannot be found here. </p>
		<p> Unfortunately we were only allowed to stay in the water for 40 minutes before we went back to Airlie Beach.
			Since the skipper gave everything again so that the boat rocked as little as possible, we decided that he definitely earned a tip.
			The price of $ 132 (approx. 90 &euro;) for this full day was absolutely justified. </p>
		<p> Back at the campsite, we all went showering to get rid of the salt water and warm up because the wind was quite fresh.
			Then we four sat together in the camp kitchen and cooked together.
			We spent the rest of the evening with chatting and playing. </p>
